<subSubSection id="DC4BFE75DBE2E424BAC5D59B07889E39" pageId="2" pageNumber="63" type="remarks">
<paragraph id="DE6CF12FC677CB399AB7A050EFC2D1FC" pageId="2" pageNumber="63">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="C7CEFC4048CDB8AD3F1531906F3F3FFB" pageId="2" pageNumber="63">
<taxonomicName id="72A767CB265B3A179B8EF18936404B06" class="Insecta" family="Heptageniidae" genus="Epeorus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Epeorus" order="Ephemeroptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="63" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Epeorus</taxonomicName>
is widely distributed in the Holarctic, northern portion of the Neotropical, Palaearctic, and Oriental regions (
<bibRefCitation id="E9C90FFEAEA0B4E6B8611E6429F7B039" author="Kluge, NY" journalOrPublisher="Kluwer Academic Publishers, Dordrecht" pageId="27" pageNumber="88" title="The Phylogenetic System of Ephemeroptera." year="2004">Kluge 2004</bibRefCitation>
). In tropical Southeast Asia, species of this genus have been reported and described by 
<bibRefCitation id="071C6AD0A152156462985B587C19C9DD" author="Braasch, D" journalOrPublisher="Reichenbachia" pageId="25" pageNumber="86" pagination="7 - 14" title="Neue Eintagsfliegen aus Thailand, nebst einigen Bemerkungen zu deren generischem Status (Insecta, Ephemeroptera: Heptageniidae)." volume="28" year="1990">Braasch (1990</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="F2D5BF98CA8D78C69F7A580104DB9BE8" author="Braasch, D" journalOrPublisher="Deutsche Entomologische Zeitschrift" pageId="25" pageNumber="86" pagination="201 - 219" title="New species of the family Heptageniidae (Ephemeroptera) from Borneo and the Philippines." url="10.1002/mmnd.201100024" volume="58" year="2011">2011</bibRefCitation>
), 
<bibRefCitation id="185EAD733BEEBF5118264D196470370A" author="Braasch, D" journalOrPublisher="Zootaxa" pageId="25" pageNumber="86" pagination="1 - 26" title="A contribution to the Heptageniidae (Insecta, Ephemeroptera) of Thailand and Malaysia." volume="2610" year="2010">Braasch and Boonsoong (2010)</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="65F25D8447A13398F2724B7BB0EF3F54" author="Braasch, D" journalOrPublisher="Reichenbachia" pageId="26" pageNumber="87" pagination="261 - 272" title="Neue Heptageniidae aus Asien (Ephemeroptera)." volume="17" year="1979">
Braasch and 
<normalizedToken id="8D21FABF9C7614B2C871ED3FA0F715B3" originalValue="Soldán">Soldan</normalizedToken>
(1979
</bibRefCitation>
, 1984c), and 
<bibRefCitation id="EBECFE02A26EB3C2CBEF9A82B5B6A36C" author="Webb, JM" journalOrPublisher="Zootaxa" pageId="28" pageNumber="89" pagination="65 - 68" title="First description of the adult male of Epeorus aculeatus Braasch (Ephemeroptera: Heptageniidae)." volume="1277" year="2006">Webb and McCafferty (2006)</bibRefCitation>
. 
<bibRefCitation id="30CF632051AC09F4CC28A2B0093DD15E" author="Nguyen, VV" journalOrPublisher="Journal of Asia-Pacific Entomology" pageId="27" pageNumber="88" pagination="19 - 28" title="Larvae of the heptageniid mayfly genus Epeorus (Ephemeroptera: Heptageniidae) from Vietnam." volume="7" year="2004 a">Nguyen and Bae (2004a)</bibRefCitation>
provided larval descriptions and a key to six species of Vietnamese 
<taxonomicName id="CEF9EAC24A2E60C3031821BB7E5BF5F4" class="Insecta" family="Heptageniidae" genus="Epeorus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Epeorus" order="Ephemeroptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="63" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Epeorus</taxonomicName>
; this was the first comprehensive taxonomic study of the larvae of 
<taxonomicName id="3116000CE52900BB88CDA4DCB60213B3" class="Insecta" family="Heptageniidae" genus="Epeorus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Epeorus" order="Ephemeroptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="63" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Epeorus</taxonomicName>
from tropical Southeast Asia. The first record of 
<taxonomicName id="8239DBC49008C4031344867CD671FE5C" class="Insecta" family="Heptageniidae" genus="Epeorus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Epeorus" order="Ephemeroptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="63" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Epeorus</taxonomicName>
in Thailand is of 
<taxonomicName id="26B65E845C30ED0AF774EC34ACD38809" class="Insecta" family="Heptageniidae" genus="Epeorus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Epeorus aculeatus" order="Ephemeroptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="63" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="aculeatus">Epeorus aculeatus</taxonomicName>
<bibRefCitation id="52A721C453C54D51CA958220BE5B6CE1" author="Braasch, D" journalOrPublisher="Reichenbachia" pageId="25" pageNumber="86" pagination="7 - 14" title="Neue Eintagsfliegen aus Thailand, nebst einigen Bemerkungen zu deren generischem Status (Insecta, Ephemeroptera: Heptageniidae)." volume="28" year="1990">Braasch (1990)</bibRefCitation>
from Doi Inthanon National Park, Chiang Mai province. Recently, the first Thai imago of 
<taxonomicName id="932C1CB7B857E93E1895F0840DCBCA57" class="Insecta" family="Heptageniidae" genus="Epeorus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Epeorus aculeatus" order="Ephemeroptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="63" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="aculeatus">Epeorus aculeatus</taxonomicName>
was described by 
<bibRefCitation id="5F5579FE90868612E4BF48C79A752F02" author="Webb, JM" journalOrPublisher="Zootaxa" pageId="28" pageNumber="89" pagination="65 - 68" title="First description of the adult male of Epeorus aculeatus Braasch (Ephemeroptera: Heptageniidae)." volume="1277" year="2006">Webb and McCafferty (2006)</bibRefCitation>
from Chiang Mai province. Originally, 
<taxonomicName id="05CD7B28299FCEE5E99EE6C3DDB0900D" class="Insecta" family="Heptageniidae" genus="Epeorus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Epeorus unicornutus" order="Ephemeroptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="63" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="unicornutus">Epeorus unicornutus</taxonomicName>
was recorded from Himalayas (
<bibRefCitation id="8C2F870D7229FDBFCD0C8368CBBDB132" author="Braasch, D" journalOrPublisher="Entomologische Nachrichten und Berichte" pageId="25" pageNumber="86" pagination="79 - 88" title="Neue Eintagsfliegen der Gattungen Epeorus und Iron aus dem Himalaja (Ephemeroptera, Heptageniidae)." volume="50" year="2006 b">Braasch 2006b</bibRefCitation>
) although it had been already collected in Thailand December 1987/1998 from the river Nam Lang, Soppong / Pangmapa, Mae Hong Son province (Braasch, unpublished). Currently, seven species of 
<taxonomicName id="5512BFFE526335BFBD7A75B21D23CC52" class="Insecta" family="Heptageniidae" genus="Epeorus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Epeorus" order="Ephemeroptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="63" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Epeorus</taxonomicName>
are known from Thailand (
<bibRefCitation id="A1CBBEC167BBFB5A2D695EF3E580859A" author="Braasch, D" journalOrPublisher="Zootaxa" pageId="25" pageNumber="86" pagination="1 - 26" title="A contribution to the Heptageniidae (Insecta, Ephemeroptera) of Thailand and Malaysia." volume="2610" year="2010">Braasch and Boonsoong 2010</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<caption id="44DF4F69C83877B0A21ABF74BCC7793E" pageId="2" pageNumber="63">
<paragraph id="1A2E4CFCB2D973EDCA6E30650000EFCD" pageId="2" pageNumber="63">
Figure 1. A Habitus of 
